import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score
In [37]:
sns.pairplot(data)
plt.title("Pairplot of the dataset")
plt.show()
In [38]:
X = data.drop("output", axis=1)
y = data["output"]
In [39]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X,y,test_size=0.2, random_state=40)
In [40]:
lr = LinearRegression()
In [41]:
lr_model = LinearRegression()
lr_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
lr_predictions = lr_model.predict(X_test)
In [42]:
lr_mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, lr_predictions)
lr_r2 = r2_score(y_test, lr_predictions)
print("Linear Regression Evaluation:")
print(f"Mean Squared Error: {lr_mse}")
print(f"R-Squared: {lr_r2}")

Linear Regression Evaluation:
Mean Squared Error: 0.0976598362483842
R-Squared: 0.6006678563953433
In [43]:
rf_model = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=42)
rf_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
rf_predictions = rf_model.predict(X_test)
In [44]:
rf_mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, rf_predictions)
rf_r2 = r2_score(y_test, rf_predictions)
print("\nRandom Forest Regressor Evaluation:")
print(f"Mean Squared Error: {rf_mse}")
print(f"R-Squared: {rf_r2}")

Random Forest Regressor Evaluation:
Mean Squared Error: 0.1069622950819672
R-Squared: 0.56263
In [45]:
print("\nModel Comparison:")

print(f"Random Forest Regressor - MSE: {rf_mse}, R2: {rf_r2}")

param_grid = {
    'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200],
    'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30],
    'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10],
    'min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 4]
}
grid_search = GridSearchCV(
    estimator=RandomForestRegressor(random_state=42),
    param_grid=param_grid,
    scoring='r2',
    cv=3,
    verbose=1,
    n_jobs=-1
)
grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)

In [50]:
